# Coding Standards

## Principle

LLM-optimized codebase. Small files, typed interfaces, no leaked secrets.

---

## Limits (enforced by `./agent lint`)

| Scope | lines | functions | classes | func_lines | imports |
|-------|-------|-----------|---------|------------|---------|
| src/**/*.py | 200 | 7 | 3 | 50 | 15 |
| tests/**/*.py | 300 | 25 | 5 | 50 | 15 |
| **/*.md, **/*.mdc | 150 | — | — | — | — |

---

## Rules

- Module docstring required for every .py file
- Type hints required on public function signatures (not `_private`)
- Linter reads .gitignore and skips excluded paths

---

## When lines > limit

Split into submodules with single responsibility.

## When functions > limit

Extract to separate module.
